y different answers to such questions. The first part of the book focuses on theoretical and conceptual issues, the second part considers processes of formal and informal regulation, while the third part examines social and political responses to industrialised food production and mass consumption. Qualities of food will be of interest to researchers and students in all the social science disciplines that are concerned with food, whether marketing, sociology, cultural studies, anthropology, human nutrition or economics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFood industry and trade. 0aFoodxAnalysis. 0aFoodxQuality. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aEuropean Food Safety Authority.  aEuropean Union.  aFood Standards Agency.  aMaghrebi Muslims.  aUnited Kingdom.  acognitive paradigms.  aeconomic competitiveness.  afood consumption.  afood production.  afood quality.  afood taste.  ahalal.  apolicy failure.  apolitical morality.1 aAllaire, Gilles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarling, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBergeaud-Blackler, Florence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGronow, Jukka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarvey, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarvey, Mark, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHennion, Antoine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarsden, Terry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcMeekin, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.g